10/10/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Investigators from the office of The Hague war crimes tribunal in Zagreb questioned the editor in chief of the local Slobodna Dalmacija daily on Tuesday (October 9th), over the May publication of classified information related to the court's activities. Mladen Plese, along with the former editor in chief of state-run Croatian Television, Vladimir Roncevic, have been charged with publishing parts of the indictments against Croat generals Ante Gotovina, Ivan Cermak and Mladen Markac, which were marked top secret at the time. (HRT, B92, Beta, AP, International Herald Tribune - 09/10/07)
